                        <interp inst="t18450707-name-432" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS ZINZAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 67.) I received the prisoner into custody at his master's shop on the 21st of June—I did not say anything to him to induce a conversation with him, but he said of his own accord that he had been robbed of 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. of the money in the Pavillion Theatre—he did not say what had become of the other 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—there was only 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. found upon him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I have no friends; I spent half the money, and the other half I was robbed of.</p>
